## Fix 3: Pull-over-push payment queue
SimpleDAO_PullPayment: 0x5FbDB2315678afecb367f032d93F642f64180aa3
Victim deposits 10 ETH. DAO balance before attack attempt: 10.0 ETH
Attack transaction completed, but no Ether was pushed to the attacker during withdraw().
DAO balance after attack attempt: 11.0 ETH
Attacker contract balance after attack attempt: 0.0 ETH
Recursive calls observed by attacker contract: 0
Pending pull payment for attacker contract after withdraw(): 1.0 ETH
[assertion ok] pull-payment records attacker seed as pending instead of pushing Ether: 1.0 ETH
Pending pull payment for legitimate victim after withdraw(2 ETH): 2.0 ETH
[assertion ok] legitimate user can create a pull-payment claim: 2.0 ETH
Pending pull payment for legitimate victim after claimPayment(): 0.0 ETH
[assertion ok] legitimate claim clears pending payment: 0.0 ETH
[assertion ok] SimpleDAO_PullPayment final DAO balance matches protected-flow expectation: 9.0 ETH
[assertion ok] SimpleDAO_PullPayment attacker received no pushed Ether: 0.0 ETH

Result: fixed variants prevent the vulnerable drain path. CEI and guard revert the reentrant attempt; pull-over-push avoids the callback entirely.
